1. **New unit test** in `test/commands/project/list.test.ts`:
   - **"bare slug matching cached org auto-redirects to org-all"**: Seed the org cache with `{ slug: "ftmo" }`, mock fetch to 404 on `getProject` but return projects on org-all listing. Call `handleProjectSearch("ftmo", flags)` — but actually, the better test is to exercise the full `dispatchOrgScopedList` path with `orgSlugFallback: "redirect"` to confirm the pre-check fires.

2. **New unit test** in a shared test file (e.g., `test/lib/org-list.test.ts`):
   - **"orgSlugFallback redirect converts project-search to org-all"**: Seed org cache, call `dispatchOrgScopedList` with `orgSlugFallback: "redirect"` and verify org-all handler is invoked.
   - **"orgSlugFallback error throws ResolutionError"**: Same setup but with `"error"`.
   - **"no orgSlugFallback skips pre-check"**: Verify the project-search handler runs when option is omitted.

3. **Existing tests pass**: `bun test test/commands/project/list.test.ts` — the existing "not found throws ResolutionError" test (line 639) still passes because its mock org slug is `"test-org"` and search slug is `"nonexistent"` (no match).

